php-vitexsoftware-multiflexi-core (2.10.0) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * fix(packaging): remove stale duplicate VaultWarden CredentialProtoType, its
    credprototype.json and test — this credential type is owned by the standalone
    multiflexi-vaultwarden package; the copy here was outdated and collided at
    /usr/share/php/MultiFlexi/CredentialProtoType/VaultWarden.php during install
  * test: drop AutoloadAndInheritanceTest.php entries and leftover
    CredentialProtoType{AbraFlexi,Csas,RaiffeisenBank,mServer}Test.php files for
    credential types that were already split into their own add-on packages
    (multiflexi-abraflexi, multiflexi-csas, multiflexi-raiffeisenbank,
    multiflexi-mserver) — these classes no longer exist in core and made the
    test suite fatal when run without those packages installed
  * fix: Company::takeData() always set enabled=true when key present; use !empty() to respect actual value
  * Add CredentialState enum (Available/Degraded/Unavailable/Misconfigured/Unknown)
  * Add CredentialCheckResult final class with isSatisfied() gate logic
  * Add checkableCredentialInterface marker interface
  * CredentialProtoType: implement checkableCredentialInterface with no-op default
    returning Unknown (backward compatible — existing prototypes never block)
  * FioBank: add checkAvailability() — validates token, probes fioapi.fio.cz reachability
    without token-scoped call (avoids 30 s rate limit and cursor side effect)
  * Job: add reportCredentialBlocked() — emits availability failure to SQL log,
    Zabbix (when ZABBIX_SERVER configured), and OpenTelemetry (when OTEL_ENABLED)
  * Add Task class with state machine (open/running/fulfilled/fulfilled_late/failed/missed)
  * Add Task::materialize(), fulfill(), markFailed(), markMissed(), canRetry(), getNextRetryTime()
  * Job: carry task_id in newJob() INSERT; drive task state transitions in runEnd()
  * RunTemplate: add getters/setters for deadline_offset, max_attempts, retry_backoff,
    retry_min_gap, allow_late
  * Application: persist produces/consumes from app.json import
  * Application: getProduces(), getConsumes(), getAppJson() includes produces/consumes
  * Job: collectProducedData() resolves produced output by format
  * EventRule: generalize buildEnvOverrides() to accept any source array
  * EventRule: add resolveSelector() with dot-path, JSONPath, @file: support
  * EventRule: add getRulesForRunTemplate() for job-completed chain triggers

